-- EBRD Lends $38.6 Million to UniCredit in Serbia for SME Firms
-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 2013-05-17T11:18:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-17/ebrd-lends-38-6-million-to-unicredit-in-serbia-for-sme-firms.html
The European Bank for Reconstruction
and Development approved 30 million-euro (38.6 million)
financing for small and medium-sized business in Serbia that
will be disbursed through the local units of  UniCredit SpA. (UCG)   The EBRD will provide another 15 million euros to UniCredit
Leasing Serbia DOO to bolster its operations in equipment
leasing, the London-based lender said in an e-mailed statement.
The funds are provided as part of EBRDâ€™s broader agreement with
the World Bank and the  European Investment Bank  on more than 30
billion euro joint commitments in eastern Europe this year and
